  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Higher model risk drives stricter credibility requirements; Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed. This package contains a version-drift weakener: the primary ValidationResult was generated under ModelConfiguration ansys-cfx-24q3-build-2 (modelVersion 2024-q3-build-2), which predates the UofA currentModelVersion 2026-q1-build-7 by approximately six quarters. The supporting validation evidence therefore no longer applies to the model of record.",
